dataIdInfo.idPurp: This is a point dataset representing natural gas transmission hubs in the continguous U.S. These data originate from the U.S. Energy Information Administration. Last updated Sept. 2009. For additional information, see "Natural Gas Market Centers: A 2008 Update": http://www.eia.gov/pub/oil_gas/natural_gas/feature_articles/2009/ngmarketcenter/ngmarketcenter.pdf
dataIdInfo.idAbs: A hub is a physical transfer point for natural gas where several pipelines are connected. A market center is a hub where the operator offers services that facilitate the buying, selling, and transportation of natural gas.
